-- Deutsche Bank’s Sal. Oppenheim Unit Cuts Advisers, FTD Reports
-- B y   C o r n e l i u s   R a h n
-- 2012-03-15T20:16:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-15/deutsche-bank-s-sal-oppenheim-unit-cuts-advisers-ftd-reports.html
Deutsche Bank AG (DBK) ’s Sal. Oppenheim
wealth-management unit is cutting 12 of about 100 client
advisers after introducing stricter performance measurements,
 Financial Times Deutschland  reported, citing unidentified people
in the financial market.  Some of those asked sign termination agreements have
already left the bank, the newspaper said. Sal. Oppenheim
confirmed the introduction of the new benchmarks, the FTD
reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Cornelius Rahn in Frankfurt at 
